blockSize

public int blockSize

Size of buffer in number of record. Negative value means no buffer.

The buffer is used in order to write by block in file. The record is generated in memory into buffer. When the buffer is full, we flush the buffer in file.

By default -1.

Since:
0.0.1

isAsynchronousWrite

public boolean isAsynchronousWrite
True if you want to write file asynchronously. You can define the number of thread dedicate to write file in FactoryCsvWriter. By default the number of processor divide by 3. If you create several files in the same time, the threads will be share for each files.

Since:
0.0.1

header

public String header
the header of CSV file generated. The header is generated with the name of field. If no name is defined for a field, we take the property name or method name. If a custom header is defined, its value is append to variable header

Since:
0.0.1

isAppendToFile

public boolean isAppendToFile

True if you want to append csv data to a file (if it exist). If the file doesn't exist, it create a new file.

False, if you already want to create a new file. By default, it's false.

Since:
0.0.1

commentCharacter

public char commentCharacter
Define the character in order to comment a line or data. Each comments will be write on a new line. If a field value has carriage return, a comment character will be added after the carriage return. By default 35

0.1.0

maxRecordByFile

public long maxRecordByFile

maxFileSize

public long maxFileSize
The default max size of file. By default -1. If the max size is negative, no max size is defined. The size is defined in byte.

isFileByFile

public boolean isFileByFile
If CsvBang must process file one by one or multiple file. This option is active only if a max number of files in pool is defined. By default, it's value is true.

0.1.0
